# Supabase Migration + Vercel Deploy — Implementation Plan

Migrates the ÓticaSystem from localStorage-based fake persistence to real Supabase (Postgres + Auth + RLS), then deploys to Vercel. The build step runs the migration script automatically, keeping the process CI-friendly and idempotent.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Before running the build**, you must:
> 1. Create a Supabase project and copy the Project URL, Anon Key, and Database URL from the dashboard.
> 2. Create a `.env` file at the project root (copy from `.env.example`) and fill in the three variables.
> 3. After the first build/migrate, manually create the four auth users in the Supabase dashboard and run the `INSERT INTO profiles` SQL (as explained in Step 6 of the request).

> [!WARNING]
> The existing [useStore.js](file:///c:/Users/Cris/Documents/gravity/src/store/useStore.js) will be **replaced** by a new `authStore.js`. All pages that currently call `useStore()` will be updated to use the new store + service layer. There is no automated rollback — make sure you have the current code committed to Git before proceeding.

## Proposed Changes

### Dependencies

#### [MODIFY] package.json

- Add `@supabase/supabase-js` and `pg` to `dependencies`
- Change `"build"` script to `"node scripts/migrate.js && vite build"` (already has `"type": "module"`)

---

### Integration Layer

#### [NEW] src/lib/supabase.js
Creates the Supabase client using `VITE_SUPABASE_URL` and `VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY`.

#### [NEW] scripts/migrate.js
Node.js ES module script that connects via `DATABASE_URL` (pg) with SSL, executes the full idempotent SQL (tables, triggers, RLS policies, views, seed data), and calls `process.exit(0)` on success.

---

### State & Services (replaces useStore.js)

#### [NEW] src/store/authStore.js
Zustand store managing Supabase Auth session:
- [loginMaster(email, password)](file:///c:/Users/Cris/Documents/gravity/src/store/useStore.js#16-24) — `signInWithPassword` + validates `role === 'master'` in `profiles`
- [loginUnit(email, password, slug)](file:///c:/Users/Cris/Documents/gravity/src/store/useStore.js#25-41) — same, validates `role === 'unit'` and unit slug
- [logout()](file:///c:/Users/Cris/Documents/gravity/src/store/useStore.js#43-44) — `supabase.auth.signOut()`
- `init()` — `getSession()` + `onAuthStateChange` listener
- State: `{ user, profile, unit, session, loading }`

#### [NEW] src/services/clientService.js
Pure async functions (not Zustand):
- [getClients(unitId, filters)](file:///c:/Users/Cris/Documents/gravity/src/store/useStore.js#80-86) — select with optional status/name filters
- `getClientById(id)` — includes `status_history(*)`
- [createClient(unitId, data)](file:///c:/Users/Cris/Documents/gravity/src/store/useStore.js#91-112) — insert + create first status_history entry
- [updateClient(id, updates)](file:///c:/Users/Cris/Documents/gravity/src/store/useStore.js#113-126) — simple update
- `updateClientStatus(client, newStatus, note)` — update status + insert status_history
- [deleteClient(id)](file:///c:/Users/Cris/Documents/gravity/src/store/useStore.js#127-132) — delete
- `getUnitMetrics(unitId)` — aggregate query for dashboard cards

#### [NEW] src/services/unitService.js
Pure async functions:
- `getAllUnits()` — reads `unit_summary` view
- `getUnitBySlug(slug)` — reads `units` table
- [createUnit(data)](file:///c:/Users/Cris/Documents/gravity/src/store/useStore.js#52-65) — insert
- `toggleUnitActive(id, active)` — update `active` column
- [getNotifications(unitId)](file:///c:/Users/Cris/Documents/gravity/src/store/useStore.js#133-139) — `unit_id = unitId OR unit_id IS NULL`
- `createNotification({ unitId, title, message, type })` — insert
- `markNotificationRead(id)` — update `read = true`

---

### Pages (updated to async Supabase calls)

All pages currently import `useStore`. They will be migrated to:
- Use `useAuthStore` (Zustand) for auth state
- Call `clientService.*` / `unitService.*` directly with `useEffect` + local state

#### [MODIFY] src/App.jsx
- Call `authStore.init()` on mount via `useEffect`
- Updated route guards: check `authStore.profile.role` instead of `masterAuth`/`unitAuth`
- Show loading spinner while session is being restored

#### [MODIFY] src/pages/master/MasterLogin.jsx
- Calls `authStore.loginMaster(email, password)` (async)
- Shows proper error messages from Supabase

#### [MODIFY] src/pages/master/MasterDashboard.jsx
- Reads `unitService.getAllUnits()` in `useEffect`
- Sends notifications via `unitService.createNotification()`
- Toggles active via `unitService.toggleUnitActive()`
- Logout via `authStore.logout()`

#### [MODIFY] src/pages/master/UnitsList.jsx
- Reads from `unitService.getAllUnits()`

#### [MODIFY] src/pages/master/NewUnit.jsx
- Creates via `unitService.createUnit(data)`

#### [MODIFY] src/pages/unit/UnitLogin.jsx
- Fetches unit info via `unitService.getUnitBySlug(slug)` in `useEffect`
- Calls `authStore.loginUnit(email, password, slug)` (async)

#### [MODIFY] src/pages/unit/UnitDashboard.jsx
- Fetches metrics via `clientService.getUnitMetrics(unitId)` or `clientService.getClients(unitId)`
- Gets `unitId` from `authStore.profile.unit_id`

#### [MODIFY] src/pages/unit/ClientsPanel.jsx
- Calls `clientService.getClients(unitId, { status, name })` in `useEffect`

#### [MODIFY] src/pages/unit/ClientForm.jsx
- Calls `clientService.createClient` / [updateClient](file:///c:/Users/Cris/Documents/gravity/src/store/useStore.js#113-126)

#### [MODIFY] src/pages/unit/ClientDetails.jsx
- Calls `clientService.getClientById(id)` and `clientService.updateClientStatus()`

#### [MODIFY] src/pages/unit/CRMPage.jsx
- Reads from `clientService.getClients()` + reformats for CRM display

